<asp:Content ContentPlaceHolderID="title" runat="server">
    <h4>
        Alienation</h4>
    <h3>
        That relationship with God was broken by sinful rebellion.</h3>
</asp:Content>
<asp:Content ID="TextContent" ContentPlaceHolderID="text" runat="Server">
    <p>
        The same opening chapters of the Bible that describe personal and intimate relationship
        of people with their Creator also tell of the <span style="font-style: italic;">tragedy</span>
        of that relationship being broken by sin. This account is not only an event of history,
        it the story of every ordinary human being since.<a href="scripture.ashx?ref=Romans+5:12-21&height=300&width=300"
            title="Romans 5:12-21" style="text-decoration: none;" class="thickbox"><img src="..\images\book_rpc.JPG" style="border:none;" /></a>
        Because of those events every one of us is a sinner, in rebellion against God, in
        violation of his moral law, in danger of eternal punishment, in desperate need of
        salvation, and deprived of true life. The Bible declares in sweeping terms:</p>
    <blockquote>
        All have sinned and fall short of the glory of God.<a href="scripture.ashx?ref=Romans+3:23&height=300&width=300"
            title="Romans 3:23" style="text-decoration: none;" class="thickbox"><img src="..\images\book_rpc.JPG" style="border:none;" /></a></blockquote>
    <blockquote>
        Your iniquities have made a separation between you and your God; your sins have
        hidden his face from you.<a href="scripture.ashx?ref=Isaiah+59:2&height=300&width=300"
            title="Isaiah 59:2" style="text-decoration: none;" class="thickbox"><img src="..\images\book_rpc.JPG" style="border:none;" /></a></blockquote>
    <p>
        This broken relationship with God has left all of us lacking and looking&mdash; lacking
        in the joy and meaning of lives lived with God and looking for some way to fill
        that void. The image of God in us is now deformed and defaced.</p>
    <div style="padding-left: 1em;">
        <ul>
            <li>Now our lives are characterized by <span style="font-style: italic;">hollowness</span>.
                We have lost that meaning, purpose, and identity that were part of God's design
                in relationship with him. A void exists in the very center of our beings in our
                separation from God by sin. Of course, voids seek to be filled; they <span style="font-style: italic;">
                    motivate</span> us to fill them.<a href="scripture.ashx?ref=Isaiah+55:1-2&height=300&width=300"
                        title="Isaiah 55:1-2" style="text-decoration: none;" class="thickbox"><img src="..\images\book_rpc.JPG" style="border:none;" /></a>
                And so we try to find satisfaction in all sorts of things&mdash;career, material possessions,
                money, educational degrees, appearance, athletics, religious practices and involvement,
                and the list goes on.</li>
            <li>We are <span style="font-style: italic;">helpless</span> to deal with this sin that
                grips us. God is holy.<a href="scripture.ashx?ref=Psalm+99:9&height=300&width=300"
                    title="Psalm 99:9" style="text-decoration: none;" class="thickbox"><img src="..\images\book_rpc.JPG" style="border:none;" /></a> He
                is perfectly and morally pure and cannot tolerate sin.<a href="scripture.ashx?ref=Psalm+5:4-6&height=300&width=300"
                    title="Psalm 5:4-6" style="text-decoration: none;" class="thickbox"><img src="..\images\book_rpc.JPG" style="border:none;" /></a> Our
                predicament is not just our sin but our sinfulness. We sin because we are sinners.<a
                    href="scripture.ashx?ref=Psalm+51:5;+Matthew+15:18-19&height=300&width=300" title="Psalm 51:5; Matthew 15:18-19"
                    style="text-decoration: none;" class="thickbox"><img src="..\images\book_rpc.JPG" style="border:none;" /></a> We break God's law by
                what we do <a href="scripture.ashx?ref=1+John+3:4&height=300&width=300" title="1 John 3:4"
                    style="text-decoration: none;" class="thickbox"><img src="..\images\book_rpc.JPG" style="border:none;" /></a> and what we fail to do,<a href="scripture.ashx?ref=James+4:17&height=300&width=300"
                        title="James 4:17" style="text-decoration: none;" class="thickbox"><img src="..\images\book_rpc.JPG" style="border:none;" /></a>
                not only in action,<a href="scripture.ashx?ref=Matthew+12:36;+Romans+13:9&height=300&width=300"
                    title="Matthew 12:36; Romans 13:9" style="text-decoration: none;" class="thickbox"><img src="..\images\book_rpc.JPG" style="border:none;" /></a>
                but even in our thoughts.<a href="scripture.ashx?ref=Matthew+5:21-22,+27-28&height=300&width=300"
                    title="Matthew 5:21-22, 27-28" style="text-decoration: none;" class="thickbox"><img src="..\images\book_rpc.JPG" style="border:none;" /></a>
                There is nothing we can do, either to <span style="font-style: italic;">make up</span>
                for the guilt of our past sin or to <span style="font-style: italic;">measure up</span>
                to God's unchanging standard of perfection<a href="scripture.ashx?ref=James+2:10;+Isaiah+64:6-7;+Romans+3:19-20&height=300&width=300"
                    title="James 2:10; Isaiah 64:6-7; Romans 3:19-20" style="text-decoration: none;"
                    class="thickbox"><img src="..\images\book_rpc.JPG" style="border:none;" /></a> that he requires.</li>
            <li>We are left <span style="font-style: italic;">hopeless</span>. Incapable of dealing
                with the condition of sin in our lives, we can only expect the punishment of God
                upon us for our sin.<a href="scripture.ashx?ref=John+3:17-18,36;+Hebrews+10:31;+Isaiah+6:3-5&height=300&width=300"
                    title="John 3:17-18,36; Hebrews 10:31; Isaiah 6:3-5" style="text-decoration: none;"
                    class="thickbox"><img src="..\images\book_rpc.JPG" style="border:none;" /></a> Not only are we without God and without hope in this
                life,<a href="scripture.ashx?ref=Ephesians+2:12&height=300&width=300" title="Ephesians 2:12"
                    style="text-decoration: none;" class="thickbox"><img src="..\images\book_rpc.JPG" style="border:none;" /></a> the gavel of God's judgment
                on us as violators of his moral law is poised to fall at our physical death.<a href="scripture.ashx?ref=Hebrews+9:27&height=300&width=300"
                    title="Hebrews 9:27" style="text-decoration: none;" class="thickbox"><img src="..\images\book_rpc.JPG" style="border:none;" /></a> God's
                pronouncement of "guilty" hangs over our heads and his sentence of eternal separation
                looms before us.<a href="scripture.ashx?ref=2+Thessalonians+1:8-10&height=300&width=300"
                    title="2 Thessalonians 1:8-10" style="text-decoration: none;" class="thickbox"><img src="..\images\book_rpc.JPG" style="border:none;" /></a></li>
        </ul>
        <br />
    </div>
</asp:Content>
<asp:Content ID="Content3" ContentPlaceHolderID="EndParagraph" runat="server">
    <p>
        What a tragic and terrifying predicament! In our separation from God we live an
        awkward and anemic life in this world, trying to make the best of things, satisfying
        ourselves with temporary and illusory measures.<a href="scripture.ashx?ref=Ecclesiastes+2:10-11&height=300&width=300"
            title="Ecclesiastes 2:10-11" style="text-decoration: none;" class="thickbox"><img src="..\images\book_rpc.JPG" style="border:none;" /></a>
        We are impotent to deal with the guilt of sin that condemns <a href="scripture.ashx?ref=Romans+3:9,19&height=300&width=300"
            title="Romans 3:9,19" style="text-decoration: none;" class="thickbox"><img src="..\images\book_rpc.JPG" style="border:none;" /></a>
        us and the power of sin that enslaves<a href="scripture.ashx?ref=Romans+6:16&height=300&width=300"
            title="Romans 6:16" style="text-decoration: none;" class="thickbox"><img src="..\images\book_rpc.JPG" style="border:none;" /></a> us.
        (What's sin all about? See <a id="A1" href="faqsin.aspx" runat="server">sin FAQs</a>)</p>
